    • Method Detail

      • getReferences

        Iterable<String> getReferences()
        Get the references that are used to iterate through the items. Implementations are free to skip references and/or produce 1 or more items for each reference. The Strings returned must be dereferencable through the dereference(List) and dereference(String) methods.
        Returns:
        an iterable that produces references in an order used to produce the items that are available from the iterator.

      • dereference

        T dereference(String reference)
        Get the item(s) at the underlying reference.
        Parameters:
        reference - a reference string, presumably one that is a member of the iterable returned by getReferences().
        Returns:
        null is supported but may trigger a NoSuchElementException elsewhere, such as dereference(List).

      • dereference

        List<T> dereference(List<String> references)
        Get the item(s) at the underlying reference. Implementations may choose to loop on dereference(String) or in some cases it may be more efficient to dereference in bulk.
        Parameters:
        reference - a reference string, presumably one that is a member of the iterable returned by getReferences().
        Returns:
        a list of dereferenced items in 1:N correspondence with the input references.
